flowRoot.flowPara: Entity API shows user a web form with structured fields, options and helpful submission information.
All the forms share the same API to make each element solid, decoupled and reusable across the site.
Validation API ensures that all the fields that have special needs (eg required, unique values etc) will get the correct data.
Data, finally, get into the Database through the secure Database API.
Validates user input before sending data to the Entity Validation API. Users cannot "mess things" with HTML.
The CKEditor WYSIWYG is available for the user. Nice buttons and popups make authoring easy.
Drupal checks if current user has the permissions to access the form and input data on the fields.
API and UI where users can upload, manage and reuse images, files, videos, embeds and other multimedia assets.
